<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
This species differs from the Nepalese 
<taxonomicName family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="C." lsidName="C. meleagris" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="meleagris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">C. meleagris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having heart-shaped leaves, a small and narrowed upper part of corolla tube, corolla lobes coherent at the top to form a pentagonal canopy and glabrous internal surface of corolla. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="C." lsidName="C. dorjei" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="dorjei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">C. dorjei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having smaller corolla and differs from 
<taxonomicName family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="C." lsidName="C. aridicola" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" rank="species" species="aridicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">C. aridicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
W. W. 
<pageBreakToken pageId="2" pageNumber="43" start="start">Smith</pageBreakToken>
by having a different shape of leaf apex, smaller flower, different corolla color and canopy structure.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
