<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. T. Liu &amp; Z. K. Wu" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="Ceropegia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceropegia jinshaensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinshaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Ceropegia jinshaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is named after its type locality, which lies along the Jinsha River.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="vernacular name">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Vernacular name.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Chinese mandarin: jin sha jiang diao deng hua (金沙江吊灯花).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="phenology">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">This new species was observed flowering from July to August and fruiting from August to October.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. T. Liu &amp; Z. K. Wu" authorityYear="2019" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asclepiadaceae" genus="Ceropegia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ceropegia jinshaensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jinshaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Ceropegia jinshaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known from two localities in NW Yunnan and grows on the open stony slope of dry-hot valley along the Jinsha River dominant by 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Cactaceae" genus="Opuntia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Opuntia monacantha" order="Cactales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="monacantha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Opuntia monacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Willd.) Haw., 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Verbenaceae" genus="Vitex" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vitex negundo" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="negundo">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Vitex negundo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. thicket and with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Anthony" authorityYear="1927" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Malvaceae" genus="Hibiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hibiscus aridicola" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="aridicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Hibiscus aridicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
J. Anthony, 
<taxonomicName class="Monocotyledoneae" family="Liliaceae" genus="Hemerocallis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Hemerocallis fulva" order="Liliiflorae" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Hemerocallis fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) L. and 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Meliaceae" genus="Munronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Munronia pinnata" order="Rutales" pageId="3" pageNumber="44" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="pinnata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Munronia pinnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Wall.) W. Theob.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="44" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="44">
Only known from two gatherings. The population of type locality is ca. 0.5 km downstream from the crest of Ahai dam; the original habitat could be disturbed or changed by human activities such as road expansion and other building construction. Based on the IUCN criteria 3.1 (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="South African Journal of Botany" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" refId="B4" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 3.1. Prepared by the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge." year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
), the conservation status is categorized as Critically Endangered (CR A3c+B2b (iii)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
